@IdempotencyDemo_HostAddress = http://localhost:5202

### 1. Process a payment with an idempotency key
POST {{IdempotencyDemo_HostAddress}}/payments
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: 9f4e1a2b-3c7d-4e8f-a0b1-c2d3e4f5a6b7

{
  "customerId": "cust-001",
  "amount": 99.99,
  "currency": "GBP"
}

### 2. Retry the exact same request — note Idempotency-Replayed: true in response headers
###    Payment is NOT processed again; the cached response is returned.
POST {{IdempotencyDemo_HostAddress}}/payments
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: 9f4e1a2b-3c7d-4e8f-a0b1-c2d3e4f5a6b7

{
  "customerId": "cust-001",
  "amount": 99.99,
  "currency": "GBP"
}

### 3. Same key, different body — should return 422
POST {{IdempotencyDemo_HostAddress}}/payments
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: 9f4e1a2b-3c7d-4e8f-a0b1-c2d3e4f5a6b7

{
  "customerId": "cust-001",
  "amount": 200.00,
  "currency": "GBP"
}

### 4. New key — processes a fresh payment
POST {{IdempotencyDemo_HostAddress}}/payments
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890

{
  "customerId": "cust-002",
  "amount": 49.99,
  "currency": "GBP"
}

### 5. No idempotency key — processed but not cached
POST {{IdempotencyDemo_HostAddress}}/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "cust-003",
  "amount": 9.99,
  "currency": "GBP"
}

### 6. List all payments — only unique payments appear
GET {{IdempotencyDemo_HostAddress}}/payments

### 7. Inspect stored idempotency keys
GET {{IdempotencyDemo_HostAddress}}/idempotency-keys
